{
  "texts": [
    "7 To reduce such security risks, training data should be appropriately curated, sourced (to avoid websites hosting sensitive content), and de-duplicated (to limit repeated inclusion of personal information).",
    "Developers and regulators can also consider audits to determine the privacy risks posed by models.",
    "Ensuring the benefits of LLMs exceed the risks will require that humans can trust, understand, and improve upon their output, and that patients and clinicians remain the principal arbiters of consequential decisions.",
    "It will also require confronting a competitive commercial landscape, in which companies face limited public oversight and have strong incentives to rapidly bring products to market.",
    "A prudent path may involve public-private research and business partnerships that help align incentives."
  ]
}